<specimenReference collectionCode="BM">
Herb. Clifford (
<collectionCode>BM</collectionCode>
)
</specimenReference>
exists, as well as a Rheede illustration, but both are sterile. Because of the importance of fruit characters, Verdcourt in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="892">Kew Bull.</emphasis>
41: 448 (1986) therefore designated a fruiting specimen (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="892">Fiori 471</emphasis>
, K) as a 
<typeStatus>
<typeStatus>neotype</typeStatus>
</typeStatus>
. Although this is contrary to Art. 9.15, 
